{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"What I want to do today is to spend"},{"time":2000,"text":"some time talking about some stuff that's"},{"time":4000,"text":"sort of giving me a little bit of"},{"time":6000,"text":"existential angst, for lack of a better word,"},{"time":9000,"text":"over the past couple of years, and"},{"time":11000,"text":"basically, these three quotes"},{"time":14000,"text":"tell what's going on."},{"time":16000,"text":"\"When God made the color purple,"},{"time":18000,"text":"God was just showing off,\" Alice Walker"},{"time":20000,"text":"wrote in \"The Color Purple,\" and"},{"time":22000,"text":"Zora Neale Hurston wrote in"},{"time":24000,"text":"\"Dust Tracks On A Road,\""},{"time":26000,"text":"\"Research is a formalized curiosity."},{"time":28000,"text":"It's poking and prying with a purpose.\""},{"time":30000,"text":"And then finally,"},{"time":32000,"text":"when I think about the near future,"},{"time":34000,"text":"you know, we have this attitude, well,"},{"time":36000,"text":"whatever happens, happens. Right?"},{"time":38000,"text":"So that goes along with the Chesire Cat"},{"time":40000,"text":"saying, \"If you don't care much"},{"time":42000,"text":"where you want to get to,"},{"time":44000,"text":"it doesn't much matter which way you go.\""},{"time":46000,"text":"But I think it does matter"},{"time":48000,"text":"which way we go, and what road we take,"},{"time":50000,"text":"because when I think about design in the"},{"time":52000,"text":"near future, what I think are the most"},{"time":54000,"text":"important issues, what's really"},{"time":56000,"text":"crucial and vital is that we need"},{"time":58000,"text":"to revitalize the arts and sciences"},{"time":60000,"text":"right now in 2002."},{"time":63000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":68000,"text":"If we describe the near future"},{"time":70000,"text":"as 10, 20, 15 years from now,"},{"time":72000,"text":"that means that what we do today"},{"time":75000,"text":"is going to be critically important,"},{"time":77000,"text":"because in the year 2015,"},{"time":79000,"text":"and the year 2020, 2025, the world"},{"time":81000,"text":"our society is going to be building on,"},{"time":83000,"text":"the basic knowledge and abstract ideas,"},{"time":85000,"text":"the discoveries that we came up with today,"},{"time":88000,"text":"just as all these wonderful things we're"},{"time":90000,"text":"hearing about here at the TED conference"},{"time":92000,"text":"that we take for granted in the world"},{"time":94000,"text":"right now, were really knowledge"},{"time":96000,"text":"and ideas that came up"},{"time":98000,"text":"in the '50s, the '60s, and the '70s."},{"time":101000,"text":"That's the substrate that we're exploiting"},{"time":104000,"text":"today, whether it's the internet,"},{"time":106000,"text":"genetic engineering, laser scanners,"},{"time":108000,"text":"guided missiles, fiber optics, high-definition"},{"time":110000,"text":"television, sensing, remote-sensing"},{"time":112000,"text":"from space and the wonderful"},{"time":114000,"text":"remote-sensing photos that we see in"},{"time":116000,"text":"3D weaving, TV programs like Tracker,"},{"time":119000,"text":"and Enterprise, CD rewrite drives,"},{"time":121000,"text":"flatscreen, Alvin Ailey's Suite Otis,"},{"time":124000,"text":"or Sarah Jones' \"Your Revolution Will Not"},{"time":127000,"text":"Be Between These Thighs,\" which"},{"time":129000,"text":"by the way was banned by the FCC,"},{"time":131000,"text":"or ska, all of these things"},{"time":133000,"text":"without question, almost without exception,"},{"time":135000,"text":"are really based on ideas"},{"time":137000,"text":"and abstract and creativity"},{"time":139000,"text":"from years before,"},{"time":141000,"text":"so we have to ask ourselves,"},{"time":143000,"text":"what are we contributing to that legacy"},{"time":145000,"text":"right now? And when I think about it,"},{"time":147000,"text":"I'm really worried. To be quite frank,"},{"time":149000,"text":"I'm concerned. I'm skeptical"},{"time":151000,"text":"that we're doing very much of anything."},{"time":154000,"text":"We're, in a sense, failing to act"},{"time":156000,"text":"in the future. We're purposefully,"},{"time":159000,"text":"consciously being laggards."},{"time":161000,"text":"We're lagging behind."},{"time":163000,"text":"Frantz Fanon, who was a psychiatrist"},{"time":165000,"text":"from Martinique, said, \"Each generation"},{"time":167000,"text":"must, out of relative obscurity,"},{"time":169000,"text":"discover its mission, and fulfill or betray it.\""},{"time":174000,"text":"What is our mission? What do we have"},{"time":176000,"text":"to do? I think our mission is"},{"time":178000,"text":"to reconcile, to reintegrate"},{"time":180000,"text":"science and the arts, because right now"},{"time":183000,"text":"there's a schism that exists"},{"time":186000,"text":"in popular culture. You know,"},{"time":188000,"text":"people have this idea that science"},{"time":190000,"text":"and the arts are really separate."},{"time":192000,"text":"We think of them as separate"},{"time":194000,"text":"and different things, and this idea was"},{"time":196000,"text":"probably introduced centuries ago,"},{"time":198000,"text":"but it's really becoming critical now,"},{"time":200000,"text":"because we're making decisions about our"},{"time":202000,"text":"society every day that,"},{"time":205000,"text":"if we keep thinking that the arts"},{"time":207000,"text":"are separate from the sciences,"},{"time":209000,"text":"and we keep thinking it's cute to say,"},{"time":211000,"text":"\"I don't understand anything about this one,"},{"time":213000,"text":"I don't understand anything about the other"},{"time":215000,"text":"one,\" then we're going to have problems."},{"time":217000,"text":"Now I know no one here at TED"},{"time":219000,"text":"thinks this. All of us, we already know"},{"time":221000,"text":"that they're very connected, but I'm going"},{"time":223000,"text":"to let you know that some folks"},{"time":225000,"text":"in the outside world, believe it or not,"},{"time":227000,"text":"they think it's neat when they say,"},{"time":229000,"text":"\"You know, scientists and science is not"},{"time":231000,"text":"creative. Maybe scientists are ingenious,"},{"time":233000,"text":"but they're not creative."},{"time":235000,"text":"And then we have this tendency, the career"},{"time":237000,"text":"counselors and various people say things"},{"time":239000,"text":"like, \"Artists are not analytical."},{"time":241000,"text":"They're ingenious, perhaps,"},{"time":244000,"text":"but not analytical,\" and"},{"time":247000,"text":"when these concepts underly our teaching"},{"time":249000,"text":"and what we think about the world,"},{"time":251000,"text":"then we have a problem, because we"},{"time":253000,"text":"stymie support for everything."},{"time":255000,"text":"By accepting this dichotomy,"},{"time":257000,"text":"whether it's tongue-in-cheek, when"},{"time":259000,"text":"we attempt to accommodate it in our world,"},{"time":261000,"text":"and we try to build our foundation"},{"time":263000,"text":"for the world, we're messing up the future,"},{"time":265000,"text":"because, who wants to be uncreative?"},{"time":267000,"text":"Who wants to be illogical?"},{"time":269000,"text":"Talent would run from either of these fields"},{"time":271000,"text":"if you said you had to choose either."},{"time":273000,"text":"Then they're going to go to something"},{"time":275000,"text":"where they think, \"Well, I can be creative"},{"time":277000,"text":"and logical at the same time.\""},{"time":279000,"text":"Now I grew up in the '60s and I'll admit it,"},{"time":281000,"text":"actually, my childhood spanned the '60s,"},{"time":284000,"text":"and I was a wannabe hippie and I always"},{"time":286000,"text":"resented the fact that I wasn't really"},{"time":288000,"text":"old enough to be a hippie."},{"time":290000,"text":"And I know there are people here, the"},{"time":292000,"text":"younger generation who want to be hippies,"},{"time":294000,"text":"but people talk about the '60s all the time,"},{"time":296000,"text":"and they talk about the anarchy"},{"time":298000,"text":"that was there, but when I think about"},{"time":300000,"text":"the '60s, what I took away from it was"},{"time":302000,"text":"that there was hope for the future."},{"time":304000,"text":"We thought everyone could participate."},{"time":306000,"text":"There were wonderful, incredible ideas"},{"time":308000,"text":"that were always percolating,"},{"time":310000,"text":"and so much of what's cool or hot today"},{"time":313000,"text":"is really based on some of those concepts,"},{"time":315000,"text":"whether it's, you know, people trying to"},{"time":317000,"text":"use the prime directive from Star Trek"},{"time":319000,"text":"being involved in things, or again that"},{"time":321000,"text":"three-dimensional weaving and"},{"time":323000,"text":"fax machines that I read about in my"},{"time":325000,"text":"weekly readers that the technology"},{"time":327000,"text":"and engineering was just getting started."},{"time":329000,"text":"But the '60s left me with a problem."},{"time":331000,"text":"You see, I always assumed I would go"},{"time":333000,"text":"into space, because I followed all of this,"},{"time":336000,"text":"but I also loved the arts and sciences."},{"time":339000,"text":"You see, when I was growing up as"},{"time":341000,"text":"a little girl and as a teenager,"},{"time":343000,"text":"I loved designing and making dogs' clothes"},{"time":345000,"text":"and wanting to be a fashion designer."},{"time":347000,"text":"I took art and ceramics. I loved dance."},{"time":350000,"text":"Lola Falana. Alvin Ailey. Jerome Robbins."},{"time":354000,"text":"And I also avidly followed the Gemini"},{"time":356000,"text":"and the Apollo programs."},{"time":359000,"text":"I had science projects and tons of astronomy"},{"time":361000,"text":"books. I took calculus and philosophy."},{"time":363000,"text":"I wondered about the infinity"},{"time":365000,"text":"and the Big Bang theory."},{"time":367000,"text":"And when I was at Stanford,"},{"time":369000,"text":"I found myself, my senior year,"},{"time":371000,"text":"chemical engineering major, half the folks"},{"time":373000,"text":"thought I was a political science and"},{"time":375000,"text":"performing arts major, which was sort of"},{"time":377000,"text":"true because I was Black Student Union President"},{"time":379000,"text":"and I did major in some other things,"},{"time":381000,"text":"and I found myself the last quarter juggling"},{"time":383000,"text":"chemical engineering separation processes,"},{"time":385000,"text":"logic classes, nuclear magnetic resonance"},{"time":387000,"text":"spectroscopy, and also producing"},{"time":389000,"text":"and choreographing a dance production,"},{"time":391000,"text":"and I had to do the lighting and the"},{"time":393000,"text":"design work, and I was trying to figure out,"},{"time":396000,"text":"do I go to New York City"},{"time":398000,"text":"to try to become a professional dancer,"},{"time":400000,"text":"or do I go to medical school?"},{"time":403000,"text":"Now, my mother helped me figure"},{"time":405000,"text":"that one out. (Laughter)"},{"time":408000,"text":"But when I went into space,"},{"time":410000,"text":"when I went into space I carried a number"},{"time":412000,"text":"of things up with me. I carried a poster"},{"time":414000,"text":"by Alvin Ailey, which you can figure out"},{"time":416000,"text":"now, I love the dance company."},{"time":418000,"text":"An Alvin Ailey poster of Judith Jamison"},{"time":420000,"text":"performing the dance \"Cry,\" dedicated to all"},{"time":422000,"text":"black women everywhere. A Bundu statue,"},{"time":424000,"text":"which was from the Women's Society"},{"time":426000,"text":"in Sierra Leone, and a certificate for the"},{"time":428000,"text":"Chicago Public School students to work to"},{"time":430000,"text":"improve their science and math,"},{"time":432000,"text":"and folks asked me,"},{"time":434000,"text":"\"Why did you take up what you took up?\""},{"time":436000,"text":"And I had to say,"},{"time":438000,"text":"\"Because it represents human creativity,"},{"time":440000,"text":"the creativity that allowed us, that we were"},{"time":442000,"text":"required to have to conceive and build"},{"time":444000,"text":"and launch the space shuttle, springs from"},{"time":447000,"text":"the same source as the imagination and"},{"time":449000,"text":"analysis it took to carve a Bundu statue,"},{"time":452000,"text":"or the ingenuity it took to design,"},{"time":455000,"text":"choreograph, and stage \"Cry.\""},{"time":458000,"text":"Each one of them are different"},{"time":460000,"text":"manifestations, incarnations, of creativity,"},{"time":463000,"text":"avatars of human creativity,"},{"time":466000,"text":"and that's what we have to reconcile"},{"time":468000,"text":"in our minds, how these things fit together."},{"time":470000,"text":"The difference between arts and sciences"},{"time":472000,"text":"is not analytical versus intuitive, right?"},{"time":475000,"text":"E=MC squared required"},{"time":478000,"text":"an intuitive leap, and then you had"},{"time":480000,"text":"to do the analysis afterwards."},{"time":482000,"text":"Einstein said, in fact, \"The most beautiful"},{"time":484000,"text":"thing we can experience is the mysterious."},{"time":487000,"text":"It is the source of all true art and science.\""},{"time":490000,"text":"Dance requires us to express and want"},{"time":492000,"text":"to express the jubilation in life, but then you"},{"time":494000,"text":"have to figure out, exactly"},{"time":496000,"text":"what movement do I do to make sure"},{"time":498000,"text":"that it comes across correctly?"},{"time":500000,"text":"The difference between arts and sciences"},{"time":502000,"text":"is also not constructive versus"},{"time":504000,"text":"deconstructive, right? A lot of people"},{"time":506000,"text":"think of the sciences as deconstructive."},{"time":508000,"text":"You have to pull things apart."},{"time":510000,"text":"And yeah, sub-atomic physics"},{"time":512000,"text":"is deconstructive. You literally try to"},{"time":514000,"text":"tear atoms apart to understand"},{"time":516000,"text":"what's inside of them. But sculpture, from"},{"time":518000,"text":"what I understand from great sculptors,"},{"time":520000,"text":"is deconstructive, because you see a piece"},{"time":522000,"text":"and you remove what doesn't"},{"time":524000,"text":"need to be there."},{"time":526000,"text":"Biotechnology is constructive."},{"time":528000,"text":"Orchestral arranging is constructive."},{"time":530000,"text":"So in fact we use constructive and"},{"time":532000,"text":"deconstructive techniques in everything."},{"time":534000,"text":"The difference between science"},{"time":537000,"text":"and the arts is not that they"},{"time":540000,"text":"are different sides of the same coin, even,"},{"time":542000,"text":"or even different parts"},{"time":544000,"text":"of the same continuum, but rather"},{"time":546000,"text":"they're manifestations of the same thing."},{"time":549000,"text":"Different quantum states of an atom?"},{"time":551000,"text":"Or maybe if I want to be more 21st century"},{"time":553000,"text":"I could say that they are different harmonic"},{"time":555000,"text":"resonances of a superstring."},{"time":557000,"text":"But we'll leave that alone. (Laughter)"},{"time":559000,"text":"They spring from the same source."},{"time":561000,"text":"The arts and sciences are avatars of"},{"time":563000,"text":"human creativity. It's our attempt"},{"time":565000,"text":"as humans to build an understanding"},{"time":567000,"text":"of the universe, the world around us."},{"time":569000,"text":"It's our attempt to influence things,"},{"time":571000,"text":"the universe internal to ourselves"},{"time":573000,"text":"and external to us."},{"time":575000,"text":"The sciences, to me, are manifestations"},{"time":577000,"text":"of our attempt to express"},{"time":580000,"text":"or share our understanding,"},{"time":582000,"text":"our experience, to influence the universe"},{"time":584000,"text":"external to ourselves."},{"time":587000,"text":"It doesn't rely on us as individuals."},{"time":589000,"text":"It's the universe, as experienced"},{"time":591000,"text":"by everyone, and the arts manifest"},{"time":593000,"text":"our desire, our attempt to share"},{"time":596000,"text":"or influence others through experiences"},{"time":599000,"text":"that are peculiar to us as individuals."},{"time":601000,"text":"Let me say it again another way:"},{"time":603000,"text":"science provides an understanding"},{"time":605000,"text":"of a universal experience, and"},{"time":608000,"text":"arts provides a universal understanding"},{"time":611000,"text":"of a personal experience."},{"time":614000,"text":"That's what we have to think about,"},{"time":616000,"text":"that they're all part of us, they're"},{"time":618000,"text":"all part of a continuum."},{"time":620000,"text":"It's not just the tools, it's not just"},{"time":622000,"text":"the sciences, you know, the mathematics"},{"time":624000,"text":"and the numerical stuff and the statistics,"},{"time":626000,"text":"because we heard, very much on this"},{"time":628000,"text":"stage, people talked about music"},{"time":630000,"text":"being mathematical. Right? Arts don't just"},{"time":632000,"text":"use clay, aren't the only ones that use clay,"},{"time":634000,"text":"light and sound and movement."},{"time":637000,"text":"They use analysis as well."},{"time":640000,"text":"So people might say, well,"},{"time":642000,"text":"I still like that intuitive versus analytical"},{"time":644000,"text":"thing, because everybody wants to do the"},{"time":646000,"text":"right brain, left brain thing, right?"},{"time":648000,"text":"We've all been accused of being"},{"time":650000,"text":"right-brained or left-brained at some point"},{"time":652000,"text":"in time, depending on who"},{"time":654000,"text":"we disagreed with. (Laughter)"},{"time":656000,"text":"You know, people say intuitive, you know"},{"time":658000,"text":"that's like you're in touch with nature,"},{"time":660000,"text":"in touch with yourself and relationships."},{"time":662000,"text":"Analytical: you put your mind to work, and"},{"time":664000,"text":"I'm going to tell you a little secret. You all"},{"time":666000,"text":"know this though, but sometimes people"},{"time":668000,"text":"use this analysis idea, that things are"},{"time":670000,"text":"outside of ourselves, to be, say, that this"},{"time":672000,"text":"is what we're going to elevate"},{"time":674000,"text":"as the true, most important sciences, right?"},{"time":677000,"text":"And then you have artists, and you all"},{"time":679000,"text":"know this is true as well,"},{"time":681000,"text":"artists will say things about scientists"},{"time":684000,"text":"because they say they're too concrete,"},{"time":686000,"text":"they're disconnected with the world."},{"time":689000,"text":"But, we've even had that here on stage,"},{"time":691000,"text":"so don't act like you don't know"},{"time":693000,"text":"what I'm talking about. (Laughter)"},{"time":695000,"text":"We had folks talking about the Flat Earth"},{"time":697000,"text":"Society and flower arrangers, so there's"},{"time":699000,"text":"this whole dichotomy that we continue"},{"time":701000,"text":"to carry along, even when we know better."},{"time":704000,"text":"And folks say we need to choose either or."},{"time":707000,"text":"But it would really be foolish to choose"},{"time":709000,"text":"either one, right?"},{"time":711000,"text":"Intuitive versus analytical?"},{"time":713000,"text":"That's a foolish choice. It's foolish,"},{"time":715000,"text":"just like trying to choose between"},{"time":717000,"text":"being realistic or idealistic."},{"time":719000,"text":"You need both in life. Why do people"},{"time":721000,"text":"do this? I'm just gonna quote"},{"time":723000,"text":"a molecular biologist, Sydney Brenner,"},{"time":725000,"text":"who's 70 years old so he can say this. He said,"},{"time":727000,"text":"\"It's always important to distinguish"},{"time":729000,"text":"between chastity and impotence.\""},{"time":731000,"text":"Now... (Laughter)"},{"time":734000,"text":"I want to share with you"},{"time":737000,"text":"a little equation, okay?"},{"time":740000,"text":"How do understanding science"},{"time":743000,"text":"and the arts fit into our lives"},{"time":745000,"text":"and what's going on and the things"},{"time":747000,"text":"that we're talking about here"},{"time":749000,"text":"at the design conference, and this is"},{"time":751000,"text":"a little thing I came up with, understanding"},{"time":753000,"text":"and our resources and our will"},{"time":755000,"text":"cause us to have outcomes."},{"time":757000,"text":"Our understanding is our science, our arts,"},{"time":759000,"text":"our religion, how we see the universe"},{"time":761000,"text":"around us, our resources, our money,"},{"time":763000,"text":"our labor, our minerals, those things"},{"time":765000,"text":"that are out there in the world we have"},{"time":767000,"text":"to work with."},{"time":769000,"text":"But more importantly, there's our will."},{"time":771000,"text":"This is our vision, our aspirations"},{"time":773000,"text":"of the future, our hopes, our dreams,"},{"time":775000,"text":"our struggles and our fears."},{"time":777000,"text":"Our successes and our failures influence"},{"time":779000,"text":"what we do with all of those, and to me,"},{"time":781000,"text":"design and engineering, craftsmanship and"},{"time":783000,"text":"skilled labor, are all the things that work on"},{"time":785000,"text":"this to have our outcome,"},{"time":787000,"text":"which is our human quality of life."},{"time":790000,"text":"Where do we want the world to be?"},{"time":792000,"text":"And guess what?"},{"time":794000,"text":"Regardless of how we look at this, whether"},{"time":796000,"text":"we look at arts and sciences are separate"},{"time":798000,"text":"or different, they're both being influenced"},{"time":800000,"text":"now and they're both having problems."},{"time":802000,"text":"I did a project called S.E.E.ing the Future:"},{"time":804000,"text":"Science, Engineering and Education, and"},{"time":806000,"text":"it was looking at how to shed light on"},{"time":808000,"text":"most effective use of government funding."},{"time":810000,"text":"We got a bunch of scientists in all stages"},{"time":812000,"text":"of their careers. They came to Dartmouth"},{"time":814000,"text":"College, where I was teaching, and they"},{"time":816000,"text":"talked about with theologians and financiers,"},{"time":818000,"text":"what are some of the issues of public"},{"time":820000,"text":"funding for science and engineering"},{"time":822000,"text":"research? What's most important about it?"},{"time":824000,"text":"There are some ideas that emerged that"},{"time":826000,"text":"I think have really powerful parallels"},{"time":828000,"text":"to the arts. The first thing they said was that"},{"time":830000,"text":"the circumstances that we find ourselves in"},{"time":832000,"text":"today in the sciences and engineering that"},{"time":834000,"text":"made us world leaders is very different"},{"time":836000,"text":"than the '40s, the '50s, and the '60s"},{"time":839000,"text":"and the '70s when we emerged"},{"time":841000,"text":"as world leaders, because we're no longer"},{"time":843000,"text":"in competition with fascism, with"},{"time":845000,"text":"Soviet-style communism, and by the way"},{"time":847000,"text":"that competition wasn't just military,"},{"time":849000,"text":"it included social competition"},{"time":851000,"text":"and political competition as well,"},{"time":853000,"text":"that allowed us to look at space"},{"time":855000,"text":"as one of those platforms to prove"},{"time":857000,"text":"that our social system was better."},{"time":860000,"text":"Another thing they talked about was the"},{"time":862000,"text":"infrastructure that supports the sciences"},{"time":864000,"text":"is becoming obsolete. We look at"},{"time":866000,"text":"universities and colleges, small, mid-sized"},{"time":869000,"text":"community colleges across the country,"},{"time":871000,"text":"their laboratories are becoming obsolete,"},{"time":874000,"text":"and this is where we train most of our"},{"time":876000,"text":"science workers and our researchers,"},{"time":878000,"text":"and our teachers, by the way,"},{"time":880000,"text":"and then that there's a media that doesn't"},{"time":882000,"text":"support the dissemination of any more than"},{"time":884000,"text":"the most mundane and inane of information."},{"time":886000,"text":"There's pseudo-science, crop circles,"},{"time":888000,"text":"alien autopsy, haunted houses,"},{"time":890000,"text":"or disasters. And that's what we see."},{"time":893000,"text":"And this isn't really the information"},{"time":895000,"text":"you need to operate in everyday life"},{"time":897000,"text":"and figure out how to participate in this"},{"time":899000,"text":"democracy and determine what's going on."},{"time":901000,"text":"They also said that there's a change"},{"time":903000,"text":"in the corporate mentality. Whereas"},{"time":905000,"text":"government money had always been there"},{"time":907000,"text":"for basic science and engineering research,"},{"time":909000,"text":"we also counted on some companies to do"},{"time":911000,"text":"some basic research, but what's happened"},{"time":913000,"text":"now is companies put more energy into"},{"time":915000,"text":"short-term product development"},{"time":917000,"text":"than they do in basic engineering"},{"time":919000,"text":"and science research."},{"time":922000,"text":"And education is not keeping up."},{"time":925000,"text":"In K through 12, people are taking out"},{"time":928000,"text":"wet labs. They think if we put a computer"},{"time":930000,"text":"in the room it's going to take the place"},{"time":932000,"text":"of actually, we're mixing the acids,"},{"time":934000,"text":"we're growing the potatoes."},{"time":936000,"text":"And government funding is decreasing"},{"time":938000,"text":"in spending and then they're saying,"},{"time":940000,"text":"let's have corporations take over,"},{"time":942000,"text":"and that's not true. Government funding"},{"time":944000,"text":"should at least do things like recognize"},{"time":946000,"text":"cost-benefits of basic science and"},{"time":948000,"text":"engineering research. We have to know"},{"time":950000,"text":"that we have a responsibility"},{"time":952000,"text":"as global citizens in this world."},{"time":954000,"text":"We have to look at the education"},{"time":956000,"text":"of humans. We need to build our resources"},{"time":958000,"text":"today to make sure that they're trained so"},{"time":960000,"text":"that they understand the importance of"},{"time":962000,"text":"these things, and we have to support"},{"time":964000,"text":"the vitality of science, and that doesn't"},{"time":966000,"text":"mean that everything has to have one thing"},{"time":968000,"text":"that's going to go on, or we know"},{"time":970000,"text":"exactly what's going to be the outcome of it,"},{"time":972000,"text":"but that we support the vitality and the"},{"time":974000,"text":"intellectual curiosity that goes along,"},{"time":976000,"text":"and if you think about those parallels"},{"time":978000,"text":"to the arts, the competition"},{"time":980000,"text":"with the Bolshoi Ballet spurred"},{"time":982000,"text":"the Joffrey and the New York City Ballet"},{"time":984000,"text":"to become better."},{"time":986000,"text":"Infrastructure museums, theaters,"},{"time":988000,"text":"movie houses across the country"},{"time":990000,"text":"are disappearing. We have more"},{"time":992000,"text":"television stations with less to watch,"},{"time":994000,"text":"we have more money spent on"},{"time":997000,"text":"rewrites to get old television programs"},{"time":1000000,"text":"in the movies."},{"time":1002000,"text":"We have corporate funding now that,"},{"time":1004000,"text":"when it goes to some company, when it"},{"time":1006000,"text":"goes to support the arts, it almost requires"},{"time":1008000,"text":"that the product be part of the picture"},{"time":1010000,"text":"that the artist draws, and we have"},{"time":1013000,"text":"stadiums that are named over and over"},{"time":1015000,"text":"again by corporations."},{"time":1017000,"text":"In Houston, we're trying to figure out"},{"time":1019000,"text":"what to do with that Enron Stadium thing."},{"time":1021000,"text":"(Laughter) And fine arts and education"},{"time":1023000,"text":"in the schools is disappearing, and we have"},{"time":1025000,"text":"a government that seems like it's gutting"},{"time":1027000,"text":"the NEA and other programs,"},{"time":1029000,"text":"so we have to really stop and think,"},{"time":1031000,"text":"what are we trying to do"},{"time":1033000,"text":"with the sciences and the arts?"},{"time":1035000,"text":"There's a need to revitalize them."},{"time":1037000,"text":"We have to pay attention to it. I just want"},{"time":1039000,"text":"to tell you really quickly what I'm doing."},{"time":1041000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":1047000,"text":"I want to tell you what I've been doing"},{"time":1049000,"text":"a little bit since... I feel this need"},{"time":1053000,"text":"to sort of integrate some of the ideas"},{"time":1055000,"text":"that I've had and run across over time."},{"time":1057000,"text":"One of the things that I found out"},{"time":1060000,"text":"is that there's a need to repair"},{"time":1062000,"text":"the dichotomy between the mind and body"},{"time":1064000,"text":"as well. My mother always told me,"},{"time":1066000,"text":"you have to be observant, know what's"},{"time":1068000,"text":"going on in your mind and your body,"},{"time":1070000,"text":"and as a dancer I had this tremendous"},{"time":1072000,"text":"faith in my ability to know my body,"},{"time":1074000,"text":"just as I knew how to sense colors."},{"time":1076000,"text":"Then I went to medical school, and I was"},{"time":1078000,"text":"supposed to just go on"},{"time":1080000,"text":"what the machine said about bodies."},{"time":1082000,"text":"You know, you would ask patients"},{"time":1084000,"text":"questions and some people would tell you,"},{"time":1086000,"text":"\"Don't, don't, don't listen to what"},{"time":1088000,"text":"the patients said.\" We know that patients"},{"time":1090000,"text":"know and understand their bodies better,"},{"time":1092000,"text":"but these days we're trying to divorce them"},{"time":1094000,"text":"from that idea. We have to reconcile the"},{"time":1096000,"text":"patient's knowledge of their body"},{"time":1098000,"text":"with physician's measurements."},{"time":1100000,"text":"We had someone talk about"},{"time":1102000,"text":"measuring emotions and getting machines"},{"time":1104000,"text":"to figure out what, to keep us"},{"time":1106000,"text":"from acting crazy. Right?"},{"time":1108000,"text":"No, we shouldn't measure,"},{"time":1110000,"text":"we shouldn't use machines"},{"time":1112000,"text":"to measure road rage and then do"},{"time":1114000,"text":"something to keep us from engaging in it."},{"time":1116000,"text":"Maybe we can have machines help us"},{"time":1118000,"text":"to recognize that we have road rage and"},{"time":1120000,"text":"then we need to know how to control that"},{"time":1122000,"text":"without the machines. We even need to be"},{"time":1124000,"text":"able to recognize that without the machines."},{"time":1126000,"text":"What I'm very concerned about"},{"time":1128000,"text":"is how do we bolster our self-awareness"},{"time":1130000,"text":"as humans, as biological organisms?"},{"time":1133000,"text":"Michael Moschen spoke of having to teach"},{"time":1135000,"text":"and learn how to feel with my eyes,"},{"time":1137000,"text":"to see with my hands."},{"time":1140000,"text":"We have all kinds of possibilities to use"},{"time":1143000,"text":"our senses by, and that's"},{"time":1145000,"text":"what we have to do."},{"time":1147000,"text":"That's what I want to do, is to try to use"},{"time":1149000,"text":"bioinstrumentation, those kind of things"},{"time":1152000,"text":"to help our senses in what we do,"},{"time":1154000,"text":"and that's the work I've been doing now as"},{"time":1157000,"text":"a company called BioSentient Corporation."},{"time":1159000,"text":"I figured I'd have to do that ad, because"},{"time":1161000,"text":"I'm an entrepreneur, because entrepreneur"},{"time":1163000,"text":"says that that's somebody who does what"},{"time":1165000,"text":"they want to do because they're not broke"},{"time":1167000,"text":"enough that they have to get a real job."},{"time":1169000,"text":"(Laughter) But that's the work I'm doing"},{"time":1171000,"text":"with BioSentient Corporation trying to figure"},{"time":1173000,"text":"out how do we integrate these things?"},{"time":1175000,"text":"Let me finish by saying that"},{"time":1177000,"text":"my personal design issue for the future"},{"time":1180000,"text":"is really about integrating, to think about"},{"time":1182000,"text":"that intuitive and that analytical."},{"time":1185000,"text":"The arts and sciences are not separate."},{"time":1189000,"text":"High school physics lesson before you"},{"time":1191000,"text":"leave. High school physics teacher used to"},{"time":1193000,"text":"hold up a ball. She would say this ball"},{"time":1195000,"text":"has potential energy, but nothing"},{"time":1197000,"text":"will happen to it, it can't do any work"},{"time":1199000,"text":"until I drop it and it changes states."},{"time":1201000,"text":"I like to think of ideas as potential energy."},{"time":1204000,"text":"They're really wonderful, but nothing"},{"time":1206000,"text":"will happen until we risk"},{"time":1209000,"text":"putting them into action."},{"time":1211000,"text":"This conference is filled"},{"time":1213000,"text":"with wonderful ideas."},{"time":1215000,"text":"We're going to share lots of things"},{"time":1217000,"text":"with people, but nothing's going to happen"},{"time":1219000,"text":"until we risk putting those ideas into action."},{"time":1222000,"text":"We need to revitalize the arts and sciences"},{"time":1224000,"text":"of today, we need to take responsibility"},{"time":1226000,"text":"for the future. We can't hide behind saying"},{"time":1228000,"text":"it's just for company profits,"},{"time":1231000,"text":"or it's just a business, or I'm an artist"},{"time":1233000,"text":"or an academician."},{"time":1235000,"text":"Here's how you judge what you're doing."},{"time":1237000,"text":"I talked about that balance between"},{"time":1239000,"text":"intuitive, analytical."},{"time":1241000,"text":"Fran Lebowitz, my favorite cynic,"},{"time":1244000,"text":"she said the three questions"},{"time":1246000,"text":"of greatest concern, now I'm going to"},{"time":1248000,"text":"add on to design, is,"},{"time":1250000,"text":"\"Is it attractive?\""},{"time":1252000,"text":"That's the intuitive."},{"time":1254000,"text":"\"Is it amusing?\" The analytical."},{"time":1257000,"text":"\"And does it know its place?\""},{"time":1259000,"text":"The balance. Thank you very much."},{"time":1262000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}